29bool DataChannelController::HasDataChannels() const {
30 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
31 return !sctp_data_channels_.empty();
32}
33
34bool DataChannelController::SendData(int sid,
35 const SendDataParams& params,
36 const rtc::CopyOnWriteBuffer& payload,
37 cricket::SendDataResult* result) {
38 if (data_channel_transport())
39 return DataChannelSendData(sid, params, payload, result);
40 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "SendData called before transport is ready";
41 return false;
42}
43
44bool DataChannelController::ConnectDataChannel(
45 SctpDataChannel* webrtc_data_channel) {
46 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
47 if (!data_channel_transport()) {
48 // Don't log an error here, because DataChannels are expected to call
49 // ConnectDataChannel in this state. It's the only way to initially tell
50 // whether or not the underlying transport is ready.
51 return false;
52 }
53 SignalDataChannelTransportWritable_s.connect(
54 webrtc_data_channel, &SctpDataChannel::OnTransportReady);
55 SignalDataChannelTransportReceivedData_s.connect(
56 webrtc_data_channel, &SctpDataChannel::OnDataReceived);
57 SignalDataChannelTransportChannelClosing_s.connect(
58 webrtc_data_channel, &SctpDataChannel::OnClosingProcedureStartedRemotely);
59 SignalDataChannelTransportChannelClosed_s.connect(
60 webrtc_data_channel, &SctpDataChannel::OnClosingProcedureComplete);
61 return true;
62}
63
64void DataChannelController::DisconnectDataChannel(
65 SctpDataChannel* webrtc_data_channel) {
66 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
67 if (!data_channel_transport()) {
68 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR)
69 << "DisconnectDataChannel called when sctp_transport_ is NULL.";
70 return;
71 }
72 SignalDataChannelTransportWritable_s.disconnect(webrtc_data_channel);
73 SignalDataChannelTransportReceivedData_s.disconnect(webrtc_data_channel);
74 SignalDataChannelTransportChannelClosing_s.disconnect(webrtc_data_channel);
75 SignalDataChannelTransportChannelClosed_s.disconnect(webrtc_data_channel);
76}
77
78void DataChannelController::AddSctpDataStream(int sid) {
79 if (data_channel_transport()) {
80 network_thread()->Invoke<void>(RTC_FROM_HERE, [this, sid] {
81 if (data_channel_transport()) {
82 data_channel_transport()->OpenChannel(sid);
83 }
84 });
85 }
86}
87
88void DataChannelController::RemoveSctpDataStream(int sid) {
89 if (data_channel_transport()) {
90 network_thread()->Invoke<void>(RTC_FROM_HERE, [this, sid] {
91 if (data_channel_transport()) {
92 data_channel_transport()->CloseChannel(sid);
93 }
94 });
95 }
96}
97
98bool DataChannelController::ReadyToSendData() const {
99 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
100 return (data_channel_transport() && data_channel_transport_ready_to_send_);
101}
102
103void DataChannelController::OnDataReceived(
104 int channel_id,
105 DataMessageType type,
106 const rtc::CopyOnWriteBuffer& buffer) {
107 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread());
108 cricket::ReceiveDataParams params;
109 params.sid = channel_id;
110 params.type = type;
111 signaling_thread()->PostTask(
112 ToQueuedTask([self = weak_factory_.GetWeakPtr(), params, buffer] {
113 if (self) {
114 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(self->signaling_thread());
115 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/11547): The data being received should be
116 // delivered on the network thread. The way HandleOpenMessage_s works
117 // right now is that it's called for all types of buffers and operates
118 // as a selector function. Change this so that it's only called for
119 // buffers that it should be able to handle. Once we do that, we can
120 // deliver all other buffers on the network thread (change
121 // SignalDataChannelTransportReceivedData_s to
122 // SignalDataChannelTransportReceivedData_n).
123 if (!self->HandleOpenMessage_s(params, buffer)) {
124 self->SignalDataChannelTransportReceivedData_s(params, buffer);
125 }
126 }
127 }));
128}
129
130void DataChannelController::OnChannelClosing(int channel_id) {
131 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread());
132 signaling_thread()->PostTask(
133 ToQueuedTask([self = weak_factory_.GetWeakPtr(), channel_id] {
134 if (self) {
135 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(self->signaling_thread());
136 self->SignalDataChannelTransportChannelClosing_s(channel_id);
137 }
138 }));
139}
140
141void DataChannelController::OnChannelClosed(int channel_id) {
142 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread());
143 signaling_thread()->PostTask(
144 ToQueuedTask([self = weak_factory_.GetWeakPtr(), channel_id] {
145 if (self) {
146 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(self->signaling_thread());
147 self->SignalDataChannelTransportChannelClosed_s(channel_id);
148 }
149 }));
150}
151
152void DataChannelController::OnReadyToSend() {
153 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread());
154 signaling_thread()->PostTask(
155 ToQueuedTask([self = weak_factory_.GetWeakPtr()] {
156 if (self) {
157 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(self->signaling_thread());
158 self->data_channel_transport_ready_to_send_ = true;
159 self->SignalDataChannelTransportWritable_s(
160 self->data_channel_transport_ready_to_send_);
161 }
162 }));
163}
164
165void DataChannelController::OnTransportClosed() {
166 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread());
167 signaling_thread()->PostTask(
168 ToQueuedTask([self = weak_factory_.GetWeakPtr()] {
169 if (self) {
170 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(self->signaling_thread());
171 self->OnTransportChannelClosed();
172 }
173 }));
174}
175
176void DataChannelController::SetupDataChannelTransport_n() {
177 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread());
178
179 // There's a new data channel transport. This needs to be signaled to the
180 // |sctp_data_channels_| so that they can reopen and reconnect. This is
181 // necessary when bundling is applied.
182 NotifyDataChannelsOfTransportCreated();
183}
184
185void DataChannelController::TeardownDataChannelTransport_n() {
186 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread());
187 if (data_channel_transport()) {
188 data_channel_transport()->SetDataSink(nullptr);
189 }
190 set_data_channel_transport(nullptr);
191}
192
193void DataChannelController::OnTransportChanged(
194 DataChannelTransportInterface* new_data_channel_transport) {
195 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread());
196 if (data_channel_transport() &&
197 data_channel_transport() != new_data_channel_transport) {
198 // Changed which data channel transport is used for |sctp_mid_| (eg. now
199 // it's bundled).
200 data_channel_transport()->SetDataSink(nullptr);
201 set_data_channel_transport(new_data_channel_transport);
202 if (new_data_channel_transport) {
203 new_data_channel_transport->SetDataSink(this);
204
205 // There's a new data channel transport. This needs to be signaled to the
206 // |sctp_data_channels_| so that they can reopen and reconnect. This is
207 // necessary when bundling is applied.
208 NotifyDataChannelsOfTransportCreated();
209 }
210 }
211}

213std::vector<DataChannelStats> DataChannelController::GetDataChannelStats()
214 const {
215 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
216 std::vector<DataChannelStats> stats;
217 stats.reserve(sctp_data_channels_.size());
218 for (const auto& channel : sctp_data_channels_)
219 stats.push_back(channel->GetStats());
220 return stats;
221}
222
223bool DataChannelController::HandleOpenMessage_s(
224 const cricket::ReceiveDataParams& params,
225 const rtc::CopyOnWriteBuffer& buffer) {
226 if (params.type == DataMessageType::kControl && IsOpenMessage(buffer)) {
227 // Received OPEN message; parse and signal that a new data channel should
228 // be created.
229 std::string label;
230 InternalDataChannelInit config;
231 config.id = params.sid;
232 if (!ParseDataChannelOpenMessage(buffer, &label, &config)) {
233 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Failed to parse the OPEN message for sid "
234 << params.sid;
235 return true;
236 }
237 config.open_handshake_role = InternalDataChannelInit::kAcker;
238 OnDataChannelOpenMessage(label, config);
239 return true;
240 }
241 return false;
242}
243
244void DataChannelController::OnDataChannelOpenMessage(
245 const std::string& label,
246 const InternalDataChannelInit& config) {
247 rtc::scoped_refptr<DataChannelInterface> channel(
248 InternalCreateDataChannelWithProxy(label, &config));
249 if (!channel.get()) {
250 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to create DataChannel from the OPEN message.";
251 return;
252 }
253
254 pc_->Observer()->OnDataChannel(std::move(channel));
255 pc_->NoteDataAddedEvent();
256}
257
258rtc::scoped_refptr<DataChannelInterface>
259DataChannelController::InternalCreateDataChannelWithProxy(
260 const std::string& label,
261 const InternalDataChannelInit* config) {
262 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
263 if (pc_->IsClosed()) {
264 return nullptr;
265 }
266
267 rtc::scoped_refptr<SctpDataChannel> channel =
268 InternalCreateSctpDataChannel(label, config);
269 if (channel) {
270 return SctpDataChannel::CreateProxy(channel);
271 }
272
273 return nullptr;
274}
275
276rtc::scoped_refptr<SctpDataChannel>
277DataChannelController::InternalCreateSctpDataChannel(
278 const std::string& label,
279 const InternalDataChannelInit* config) {
280 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
281 InternalDataChannelInit new_config =
282 config ? (*config) : InternalDataChannelInit();
283 if (new_config.id < 0) {
284 rtc::SSLRole role;
285 if ((pc_->GetSctpSslRole(&role)) &&
286 !sid_allocator_.AllocateSid(role, &new_config.id)) {
287 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "No id can be allocated for the SCTP data channel.";
288 return nullptr;
289 }
290 } else if (!sid_allocator_.ReserveSid(new_config.id)) {
291 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to create a SCTP data channel "
292 "because the id is already in use or out of range.";
293 return nullptr;
294 }
295 rtc::scoped_refptr<SctpDataChannel> channel(SctpDataChannel::Create(
296 this, label, new_config, signaling_thread(), network_thread()));
297 if (!channel) {
298 sid_allocator_.ReleaseSid(new_config.id);
299 return nullptr;
300 }
301 sctp_data_channels_.push_back(channel);
302 channel->SignalClosed.connect(pc_, &PeerConnection::OnSctpDataChannelClosed);
303 SignalSctpDataChannelCreated_(channel.get());
304 return channel;
305}
306
307void DataChannelController::AllocateSctpSids(rtc::SSLRole role) {
308 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
309 std::vector<rtc::scoped_refptr<SctpDataChannel>> channels_to_close;
310 for (const auto& channel : sctp_data_channels_) {
311 if (channel->id() < 0) {
312 int sid;
313 if (!sid_allocator_.AllocateSid(role, &sid)) {
314 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to allocate SCTP sid, closing channel.";
315 channels_to_close.push_back(channel);
316 continue;
317 }
318 channel->SetSctpSid(sid);
319 }
320 }
321 // Since closing modifies the list of channels, we have to do the actual
322 // closing outside the loop.
323 for (const auto& channel : channels_to_close) {
324 channel->CloseAbruptlyWithDataChannelFailure("Failed to allocate SCTP SID");
325 }
326}
327
328void DataChannelController::OnSctpDataChannelClosed(SctpDataChannel* channel) {
329 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
330 for (auto it = sctp_data_channels_.begin(); it != sctp_data_channels_.end();
331 ++it) {
332 if (it->get() == channel) {
333 if (channel->id() >= 0) {
334 // After the closing procedure is done, it's safe to use this ID for
335 // another data channel.
336 sid_allocator_.ReleaseSid(channel->id());
337 }
338 // Since this method is triggered by a signal from the DataChannel,
339 // we can't free it directly here; we need to free it asynchronously.
340 sctp_data_channels_to_free_.push_back(*it);
341 sctp_data_channels_.erase(it);
342 signaling_thread()->PostTask(
343 ToQueuedTask([self = weak_factory_.GetWeakPtr()] {
344 if (self) {
345 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(self->signaling_thread());
346 self->sctp_data_channels_to_free_.clear();
347 }
348 }));
349 return;
350 }
351 }
352}
353
354void DataChannelController::OnTransportChannelClosed() {
355 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
356 // Use a temporary copy of the SCTP DataChannel list because the
357 // DataChannel may callback to us and try to modify the list.
358 std::vector<rtc::scoped_refptr<SctpDataChannel>> temp_sctp_dcs;
359 temp_sctp_dcs.swap(sctp_data_channels_);
360 for (const auto& channel : temp_sctp_dcs) {
361 channel->OnTransportChannelClosed();
362 }
363}
364
365SctpDataChannel* DataChannelController::FindDataChannelBySid(int sid) const {
366 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
367 for (const auto& channel : sctp_data_channels_) {
368 if (channel->id() == sid) {
369 return channel;
370 }
371 }
372 return nullptr;
373}

375DataChannelTransportInterface* DataChannelController::data_channel_transport()
376 const {
377 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/11547): Only allow this accessor to be called on the
378 // network thread.
379 // RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread());
380 return data_channel_transport_;
381}

383void DataChannelController::set_data_channel_transport(
384 DataChannelTransportInterface* transport) {
385 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread());
386 data_channel_transport_ = transport;
387}
388
389bool DataChannelController::DataChannelSendData(
390 int sid,
391 const SendDataParams& params,
392 const rtc::CopyOnWriteBuffer& payload,
393 cricket::SendDataResult* result) {
394 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/11547): Expect method to be called on the network
395 // thread instead. Remove the Invoke() below and move assocated state to
396 // the network thread.
397 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
398 RTC_DCHECK(data_channel_transport());
399
400 RTCError error = network_thread()->Invoke<RTCError>(
401 RTC_FROM_HERE, [this, sid, params, payload] {
402 return data_channel_transport()->SendData(sid, params, payload);
403 });
404
405 if (error.ok()) {
406 *result = cricket::SendDataResult::SDR_SUCCESS;
407 return true;
408 } else if (error.type() == RTCErrorType::RESOURCE_EXHAUSTED) {
409 // SCTP transport uses RESOURCE_EXHAUSTED when it's blocked.
410 // TODO(mellem): Stop using RTCError here and get rid of the mapping.
411 *result = cricket::SendDataResult::SDR_BLOCK;
412 return false;
413 }
414 *result = cricket::SendDataResult::SDR_ERROR;
415 return false;
416}
417
418void DataChannelController::NotifyDataChannelsOfTransportCreated() {
419 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread());
420 signaling_thread()->PostTask(
421 ToQueuedTask([self = weak_factory_.GetWeakPtr()] {
422 if (self) {
423 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(self->signaling_thread());
424 for (const auto& channel : self->sctp_data_channels_) {
425 channel->OnTransportChannelCreated();
426 }
427 }
428 }));
429}

431rtc::Thread* DataChannelController::network_thread() const {
432 return pc_->network_thread();
433}
434rtc::Thread* DataChannelController::signaling_thread() const {
435 return pc_->signaling_thread();
